Hi Clownbuck -

So where is the real Value Investment - What about Cash as a "value" asset?

The material stocks and commodities in particular may have already seen their
highs and could be headed a lot lower IMO. For me, there are better rivers to
fish and my top priority now is capital preservation rather than chasing
screaming value buys.

I believe a long term (7-10 years) deflationary period is possible (maybe now
30% probability) and as a results all prices could very well be a lot lower in
the future except for bare essentials (food and AG related equities). My
strategy is to hold out on any more commodity and natural resource buys until
next year and focus on yield and different safe holding buckets for my
investment capital.

If a worst case (or even a 50% worst case), I should be able to buy some
excellent value plays w/ my cash, perhaps 30% less than the current values. I
put http://www.cumtn.com/s/index.php?id=138 on my watch list today. They own a
75% interest in Copper Mountain (w/ over 5 Billion pounds of copper in the
ground). There are many other resource rich candidate located in Australia,
Canada and the U.S (hopefully avoid political risk staying in these countries).

If the slow Euro implosion continues, the probability of a world wide recession
comes into play that could further cause economies to contract. Even more QE
may not provided the stimulus to keep the U.S. growing. Testing the 2009 lows
now becomes a real possibility.

For me, it's not worth the marginal gain chasing new value candidates at this
time. I am still 80% invested in securities and preferred stocks which I
continue to hold (they generate income and I have low cost basis). Even in the
50% worst case, I expect these stock to lose at least 30% of their value.

For now, I am just trying to find calmer waters to hide in while I wait for the
market to correct to much lower prices. The value case for me, is "Cash if
King" (or cash equivalents) and eventually in 12-18 months I believe I can buy
most equities 30% lower. I continue to build my value watch lists.

There will always be some excellent "Special Situation" opportunities. Aurcana
Corporation (AUNFF) is a silver miner I recently bought at $0.756/share. Their
chart does not look exactly like GNM.AX but it is one I continue to add to even
at current prices (AUNFF last $0.98/share). As many of the large cap stocks
fall in value, many of these smaller cap stocks become exceptionable values
too.

That's my current "value" take. Remember to maintain some cash reserves as many
of the current value buys now, will become better value buys in 12-18 months.

Disclaimer: I have been wrong in the past and will be wrong in the future. My
views constantly change and at this time, that's the way I see things playing
out.

