10.8 percent, and 41,043 containers and trailers, down 11.5 percent year over
year. Mexican railroads’ carload volume increased 4 percent to 14,349 units and
intermodal volume climbed 9.8 percent to 9,994 units.

Through 2012’s first 21 weeks, 13 reporting U.S., Canadian and Mexican
railroads originated 7,820,200 carloads, down 1.8 percent, and 6,074,378
containers and trailers, up 4.1 percent compared with volumes from the same
2011 period.
interesting site
http://www.progressiverailroading.com/
