Date:6/17/2012 8:30:44 PM
From:Paul Senior
About GD: "could $64.86/share be a fairly priced stock that would offer enough
of a margin of safety? What is your opinion, value play?"

I don't know what the margin of safety is for this company because, I've no
opinion on what its business might be like if the US defense budget shrinks. On
the other hand, we (USA) seem to be in continuous, unending wars in which we
fund well our prime contractors (e.g. GD),GD also has a substantial weapons
business with foreign companies, and GD has a commercial aerospace business. (I
bought my GD shares because I like the prospects for business jet aircraft in
Asia.) On the metrics <u>I</u> look at, GD is a value play at current prices.
Because the stock itself seems to me to be cheap based on its historical
performance -- p/e, p/b, roe, etc. Not because I believe there's a margin of
safety with it at current price. The stock has been falling; I suspect it could
fall further if/as a "guns vs. butter" economic argument is made by one or
another of the USA political parties' representatives. For me, I've recently
sold my GD shares -- maybe if the stock falls further on no adverse news I
might be tempted to reenter.
