been through several of these so, I will book some of those profits now and
look to buy into many of these commodity rich companies at much lower levels
next year.

As another hedge for the portfolio and to protect against a sustained sell off
if we do see a world wide slow down, I have doubled up my UVXY shares that I
plan to hold. These should lose 2% of their value every month but do not expire
like a PUT option. I expect market volatility to accelerate if we see Oil sell
off and this hedge should help reduce my paper losses on the oil stocks I plan
to hold long term.

I am taking a more defensive position but still maintaining a position of 80%
equities and 20% cash. My equities consist of 15% preferred and 10% utilities.
