Date:6/21/2012 1:11:41 PM
From:Paul Senior
buying back shares lowers book value.

 If the buys are made at prices above book value/sh. If buy backs (and
subsequent share cancellations) are made below bv/sh, the buys raise bv/sh.

%EOM----------------------

%BOM---------------------
Date:6/21/2012 2:06:35 PM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
Correct. Most of the "Buffetty" companies buy shares above book value.
